            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* $9 billion for NASA Science sustains U.S. leadership against rapid Chinese expansion in lunar and Martian exploration.\n* Funding restores stability to a workforce that faced thousands of layoffs and talent loss following FY 2026 budget disruptions.\n* Adheres to National Academies' Decadal Surveys, ensuring peer-reviewed, nonpartisan scientific priorities drive federal investment.\n* Supports a 3:1 economic return by driving demand for cutting-edge R&D and high-skill manufacturing across the domestic aerospace industrial base.",
