            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Science Mission Directorate, $9,000,000,000.\n* This funding level supports NASA's Science Mission Directorate in its efforts to implement the scientific priorities of the National Academies' Decadal Surveys.",
            "rationale": "Provides the specific funding ask and account name as standard programmatic language, noting the importance of Decadal Surveys as per the advocacy talking points.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_1862520490:ecb6468a4692",
            "label": "Why is this important for NY or NY-07?",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Over $660,000 in NASA Science obligations reached NY-07 institutions between FY2023 and FY2025.\n* Supports the Research Foundation of CUNY in Brooklyn for critical research on urban heat island risks and community resiliency.\n* Funds Brooklyn-based innovation in advanced manufacturing, including CUNY's development of deployable 3D printing for construction materials.\n* Leverages major local industry partners like Honeybee Robotics, which received over $9 million in recent NASA contracts for planetary exploration technology.",
            "rationale": "Cites specific local spending totals and recipient institutions (CUNY, Honeybee Robotics) in NY-07 and Brooklyn, highlighting the practical application of their research and economic impact.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_1440345636:affdae64f7b5",
            "label": "Ties to NY and/or NY-07?",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "radio",
            "required": true,
            "options": [
              "Yes",
              "No"
